{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1141","published":"2024-02-08T11:06:55Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:19:40.887056Z","upstream":["CVE-2023-51043","CVE-2023-6531"],"summary":"kernel security update","details":"The Linux Kernel, the operating system core itself.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nIn the Linux kernel before 6.4.5, drivers/gpu/drm/drm_atomic.c has a use-after-free during a race condition between a nonblocking atomic commit and a driver unload.(CVE-2023-51043)\r\n\r\nA use-after-free flaw was found in the Linux Kernel due to a race problem in the unix garbage collector&apos;s deletion of SKB races with unix_stream_read_generic() on the socket that the SKB is queued on.(CVE-2023-6531)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"kernel","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP4","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/kernel&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["kernel-tools-devel-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debugsource-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","perf-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-source-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","kernel-devel-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-4.19.90-2402.4.0.0264.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["kernel-4.19.90-2402